  "name": "sunbar",
  "description": "Marimba and xylophone dancing in full sunshine: warm round rosewood bars and crisp bright bars tumbling over each other in pure daylight. A deep bouncy marimba bass floor grounds it; a warm soft-mallet lead tumbles the melody while a quick crisp xylophone counter-line dances above; a creamy dark marimba tone fills the sweet middle; bright xylophone pings and scattering top flicks sparkle; a warm marimba mallet-roll blooms and a shimmering wood-and-bar cluster swells; a near-dry muted bar-tap keeps the sunshine pulse and a bouncy high xylophone flick adds the bright accent. A major pentatonic, additive and clean, wood-and-bar joy — warm, bright, never dreary.",
